# UI Verification Gate

**This rule is binding.**

Whenever you make any functional changes (especially UI, API, or workflow changes), you **must** verify those changes using the development UI at **http://panel.dev.kaiad.dev** (or https://panel.dev.kaiad.dev/ depending on local proxy settings) before declaring the work as complete.

## How to Verify
1. If the `cursor-ide-browser` tool is available and capable, use it to navigate to the dev panel, log in if necessary, and interact with the feature you just changed.
2. Ensure there are no console errors and the UI behaves as expected.
3. If the browser tool is not available or the test requires manual intervention, explicitly ask the user to verify the changes in their browser at `http://panel.dev.kaiad.dev` before proceeding.

Do not say "I have completed the changes" without confirming they actually work in the live dev panel UI.